Professional Objective 
I am a resilient, strongly motivated and adaptable Computer Science student proactively seeking for 
career opportunities primarily within or outside the field of my study using the knowledge I have 
acquired in C++, Java and Python as well as other fundamental software development practices. I am 
currently focusing on the prospect of Machine Learning, Data analytics and Modelling as well as Artificial 
Intelligence, and am very keen on gaining more learning experience in the overall field of software 
development. Am also experienced in team and event management.

Academic Projects 
Haze Analysis, Prediction and Management System | Final Year Project 
Using SciPy libraries on Python and incorporating Support Vector Machines (SVM) for the model for a basic 
machine learning program to build projection data set to predict likelihood as well as the degree of haze’s API 
reading. The program would later would use a web-based application developed using Laravel to showcase as well 
as provide data for further decision-making options for users. 
 
 
 

Page 2 
Extra-Curricular Activities 
Esports Club President | UNITEN             
 
 
 
             September 2019 – Present 
Responsibility revolves around having an overview over the management and administrative operation of the club 
and providing leadership and support to all its members which includes team management, event management, 
official documents writing, and coordinated communications between University administrative board, committee 
members as well as the general students. 
Reply Challenge: Code Challenge 2020 | Participant  
 
       
 
 
      May 2020 
Participated in an international coding challenge hosted by Reply Challenge. Teamed up with international 
students to solve a coding problem which revolved around file reading, writing and algorithm development. 
ICTFF | Participant | UNITEN 
 
 
 
 
 
  
 
            October 2020 
Competed against numerous universities in a Capture The Flag competition. Managed to get fourth place after 
solving a series of cybersecurity oriented problems. 
Uniten Inside Out Virtual Fest | Program Director | UNITEN      
 
    July 2020 – August 2020 
Coordinated two events under UNITEN's INSIDE OUT programme in conjunction with Malaysia's Ministry Higher 
Education 'Jom Masuk IPT' programme. The two events, a Virtual Sharing Session as well as 3 Esports 
tournaments, were held to advertise UNITEN as the choice for furthering studies for future students
